The paper proposes a system for object recognition and interaction for a robot, which involves analyzing features of encountered objects and comparing them to known objects. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The system also enables the robot to learn object categories, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and symbolic reasoning (cs.SY). Finally, the paper is focused on robotics (cs.RO) applications, which is the most likely category.
